Dated at Southampton, on the aforesaid Friday, the Feast of St. Nicholas, in the sixteenth year of Richard II. And this deed being publicly read and heard, and the aforesaid Isabella examined alone concerning the aforesaid deed, and sworn according to the custom of the town, declares it to be her own doing, etc., without compulsion from the aforesaid Richard her husband, and requests that it be thus enrolled here in the form of a recognition according to the custom of the town aforesaid, in proof of the said deed and to the exclusion of her right and that of her heirs, according to those things which are contained in that deed, for ever. And it is accepted and enrolled according to the custom of the town.
